<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND CRANKCASE - FRONT OIL SEAL
        (Removal and Reassembly) (In Chassis) - REASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="3">
        <title>REASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Coat the I.D. of the front cover bore with Aviation Permatext #3</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position a new front oil seal onto the front crankcase seal installer body of
                <emph type="bold">ZTSE4130</emph>,
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350613">6.13</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the body of tool with crankshaft front oil seal over the end of the crankshaft.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach the bridge assembly to the engine front cover (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350614">6.14</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the square metal plate between the body and the bridge assembly. Make sure that the
                forcing screw tip engages the machined recess in the plate. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350614">6.14</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn the forcing screw until the body stops on the front cover to fully install the seal.
                Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350614">6.14</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Use of the installing tool ZTSE4130 assures the front oil seal is installed to 0.010 in. below
                        the front face of the front cover.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="ef4350612" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11100" filename="../figcg1/cg11100.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.12</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4350613" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12360a" filename="../figcg1/cg12360a.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.13</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4350614" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12361a" filename="../figcg1/cg12361a.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.14</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
